race.comment: FAN SEA DIVA (9) stepped out on her debut over this trip at Nowra two-and-a-half weeks ago and caught the eye when flashing home for fourth, after settling a mile back. Is sure to have come on from that and is drawn much kinder. Expect her to settle closer and prove very hard to stop. WRITTEN ABOUT (13) finished along FAN SEA DIVA, getting the bob for third. Is another likely improver that is sure to be very competitive. SMICHOV (5) also settled back on debut last time out but wound up strongly in the run home to finish third over 1200m at Canberra. Has ability and is among the chances. REVERBERATES (8) progressed nicely second-up when finishing third at Kembla Grange. Strips fitter and is in the mix. MILLY MOLLY MANDY (7) is knocking on the door. Comes through the same Nowra race as the top two, where she led them up. With the same forward showing, she could steal it.
